South Africa’s energy regulator on Monday invited the public to comment on a government plan to procure new nuclear capacity to come online after 2030. People can submit written comments to Nersa by February 5, after which the regulator will hold public hearings before deciding whether to support the government’s proposal to procure 2,500 megawatts (MW) of additional nuclear capacity. Black Friday SpecialGet 15% discount on our annual subscription!
